THE PILOT LANDED ON RUNWAY 05 WHICH WAS ICY AND COVERED WITH A BLANKET OF 
FRESH SNOW. HE STATED THE WIND WAS FROM 360 DEGS AT 10 KTS. HE HAD BEEN 
INFORMED OF POOR BRAKING CONDITIONS ON THE RUNWAY. THE PILOT USED MAIN 
WHEEL BRAKES AND REVERSE THRUST. THE AIRCRAFT DRIFTED OFF THE RIGHT SIDE OF 
THE RUNWAY, WHEN THE THROTTLES WERE NEUTRALIZED, INTO THE SOFT SOD 
SURFACE WHERE THE NOSE GEAR COLLAPSED AND THE NOSE SECTION IMPACTED 
THE GROUND. THE PILOT STATED SNOW COVERED A LAYER OF ICE ON THE RUNWAY. 
